<Link id="l00168" /><CodeLine lineNumber="168"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// Helper macro for checking the result of an &#39;Expected&lt;T&gt;&#39;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00169" /><CodeLine lineNumber="169"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00170" /><CodeLine lineNumber="170"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///   @code&#123;.cpp&#125;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00171" /><CodeLine lineNumber="171"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///     // function to be tested</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00172" /><CodeLine lineNumber="172"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///     Expected&lt;int&gt; myDivide(int A, int B);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00173" /><CodeLine lineNumber="173"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00174" /><CodeLine lineNumber="174"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///     TEST(myDivideTests, GoodAndBad) &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00175" /><CodeLine lineNumber="175"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///       // test good case</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00176" /><CodeLine lineNumber="176"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///       // if you only care about success or failure:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00177" /><CodeLine lineNumber="177"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///       EXPECT&#95;THAT&#95;EXPECTED(myDivide(10, 5), Succeeded());</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00178" /><CodeLine lineNumber="178"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///       // if you also care about the value:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00179" /><CodeLine lineNumber="179"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///       EXPECT&#95;THAT&#95;EXPECTED(myDivide(10, 5), HasValue(2));</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00180" /><CodeLine lineNumber="180"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00181" /><CodeLine lineNumber="181"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///       // test the error case</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00182" /><CodeLine lineNumber="182"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///       EXPECT&#95;THAT&#95;EXPECTED(myDivide(10, 0), Failed());</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00183" /><CodeLine lineNumber="183"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///       // also check the error message</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00184" /><CodeLine lineNumber="184"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///       EXPECT&#95;THAT&#95;EXPECTED(myDivide(10, 0),</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00185" /><CodeLine lineNumber="185"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///           FailedWithMessage(&quot;B must not be zero!&quot;));</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00186" /><CodeLine lineNumber="186"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///     &#125;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00187" /><CodeLine lineNumber="187"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///   @endcode</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00188" /><CodeLine lineNumber="188"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00189" /><CodeLine lineNumber="189" lineLink="#ad7631d96a0e84d84b35d854fdc88fd6f"><span class="doxyHighlightPreprocessor">#define EXPECT&#95;THAT&#95;EXPECTED(Err, Matcher)                                     \\</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00190" /><CodeLine lineNumber="190"><span class="doxyHighlightPreprocessor">  EXPECT&#95;THAT(llvm::detail::TakeExpected(Err), Matcher)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00191" /><CodeLine lineNumber="191" lineLink="#ae499a548f28c1b29799aa10a45e57198"><span class="doxyHighlightPreprocessor">#define ASSERT&#95;THAT&#95;EXPECTED(Err, Matcher)                                     \\</span></CodeLine>
